        "intro-text": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Crumbly started with our grandmother's sourdough starter and a cast-iron oven in the backyard. Today, we bake in a proper kitchen — but we still use the same starter, the same recipes, and the same belief that bread should taste like something.</p><p>We don't rush. Our sourdough ferments for 24 hours. Our croissants are laminated by hand. Our cakes are frosted to order. This is baking the way it used to be.</p>",
